#week-title("Four", "The Three-Year Tarot Review & Quarter II Preparation")

=== Core Teaching

The Tarot practice now spans two and a half years of daily or near-daily
engagement. This week, the student conducts a comprehensive review of the
Tarot journal from all three years — not to summarise or systematise it, but
to read it as a continuous narrative of the practitioner's own inner development
reflected in the cards.

The Tarot journal is, in this sense, a mirror of the Work: the cards that have
recurred most frequently, the readings that proved most prophetic, the cards
the practitioner has consistently misread or avoided — all of these are
diagnostic. The practitioner who has been maintaining an honest Tarot journal
across three years will find within it a portrait of their own alchemical
development that no other instrument could provide.

*The three-year spread.* Conduct a major spread reviewing the entire three-year
arc. Design the positions to correspond to Year One, Year Two, and Year Three
as wholes — not individual months but the essential character of each year.
What card best represents the Tyro year? The Initiate year? The Adept year
so far? What card describes where Year Three is heading?

*Preparation for Quarter II Gathering.* The student assembles: their personal
alchemical almanac for the mineral work; their personal alchemical spread with
full interpretation; and the current state of the Via Humida mineral preparation.

=== Topics This Week

- Reading the three-year Tarot journal as a continuous narrative of development
- Conducting the three-year arc spread
- Identifying recurring cards, avoided cards, and mispredicted cards as diagnostics
- Preparation for Year Three Quarter II Gathering

#inner-work[
  *The Three-Year Narrative*

  After reviewing the Tarot journal, write one paragraph: what is the essential
  narrative of the three years, as told by the cards? What theme has run
  through all three years, visible in retrospect even if not in the moment?

  This paragraph is one of the most important pieces of inner work documentation
  in the entire curriculum. Keep it in your journal where it can be read alongside
  the final letter to self at Year Three Month 12.
]

